What is NACL and SG
  -   NACL is access control at subnet level. SG is at instance level. NACL is stateless. Need to configure inbound as well as outbound for a port. SG is stateful. If inbound is allowed, outbound is also allowed.

What if an EC2 instance fails suddenly ? how will you troubleshoot ?
