What if a lambda function fails randomly ? how will you fix the issue ?
  - so, usually lambda function either makes http calls or calls an aws service. I will enable xray to trace the journey of that lambda function. Then, once I understand where there is a latency, I will try to increatse the retries and if that also does not work, I will try to increate timeout. If that also does not work, I will try to rewrite any logic that might be causing this.

What will you do if the RDS storage is full ?
  - First I will increate the storage / try to see if Ican use any ASG as an instance solution to solve the issue. NExt, I will see if there is a particular table, database or object tahts causing this and give it to the developers to analyze. Thirdly, I will create a cloudwatch metric to monitor when the storage is about to reach a threshhol.

What will you do if a developer deletes a critical resources like S3, RDS, EC2 ?
  -  I will try to recreate them from RDS snapshots, S3 prev version, EC2 AMI and so on. For longterm, I will enable IAM such that only DEvops Engineers are allowed to do so and that too via IAC terraform + GitHub workflows.

